# PR review recurring guards (BugNote)

Captured from PR #3 automated review. Run this mental checklist **before** opening or updating a PR.

## External I/O boundaries

- [ ] **Screenshot storage:** `reports.screenshot_url` stores a **private object key**, not a fetchable URL. Any OpenRouter vision block or browser-facing URL must use `signedScreenshotUrl()` (or skip image with a dossier note).
- [ ] **OpenRouter cost:** Prefer `x-openrouter-cost` or `usage.total_cost` when present; per-model fallback rates must not under-estimate analysis/fix models vs triage.

## State machine and queue

- [ ] **Side effect before promised state:** Do not set `status = 'queued'` (or similar) until a `jobs` row exists — call `enqueue` first or use a transaction.
- [ ] **Admin mutations:** Validate with `ReportStatus.safeParse` / `PipelineStage.safeParse` from `@bugnote/shared` (value imports, not `import type`).
- [ ] **List endpoints:** Cap numeric query params (`limit` ≤ 200, sane default); reject `NaN`.

## UI and packages

- [ ] **Dashboard actions:** Button labels must match the `ReportStatus` value written (no `resolved` unless added to schema).
- [ ] **Workspaces:** Do not duplicate the same package in `dependencies` and `devDependencies`.

## After external review

Log new recurring classes in `docs/retrospectives/` and extend this rule or `docs/agent/RETROSPECTIVE_LOG.md`.

See: `docs/retrospectives/2026-06-03-pr3-codex-copilot-review.md`.
